-- California Student Wounded in Taft High School Shooting, AP Says
-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 2013-01-10T19:03:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-10/california-student-wounded-in-taft-high-school-shooting-ap-says.html
A student was shot today at Taft
Union High School in  California ’s San Joaquin Valley and the
suspected shooter is in custody, the Associated Press reported,
citing authorities.  The student wounded in the shooting around 9 a.m. local
time was flown to a hospital in Bakersfield, Kern County
Sheriff’s Department spokesman Ray Pruitt said, according to the
report. The victim’s condition wasn’t immediately available and
the suspect is believed to be a student, the AP said.  Taft, about 120 miles northwest of Los Angeles by road,
has a population of about 18,000, according to the Taft Chamber
of Commerce’s website.  Pruitt said a shotgun is believed to have been used in the
attack, the AP said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
